#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:58
msgid ""
"Normalized percentage (0% to 100%) of the remaining space capacity. If "
"Available Spare is lower than Available Space Threshold, the drive is "
"considered to be in a critical state."
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:62
msgid ""
"Normalized percentage (0% to 100%). If the Available Spare is lower than "
"this threshold, the drive is considered to be in a critical state."
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:65
msgid ""
"Vendor-specific estimate of the percentage of device life based on the "
"actual device usage and the manufacturer's prediction of the device life. A "
"value of 100 indicates that the estimated endurance of the device has been "
"consumed, but may not indicate a device failure. This value is allowed to "
"exceed 100. Percentage values greater than 254 are be represented as 255. "
"This value is updated once per power-on hour (when the controller is not in "
"a sleep state)."
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:71
msgid ""
"The number of 512-byte data units the host has read from the controller. "
"This value does not include metadata. The value is reported in thousands "
"(i.e. a value of 1 corresponds to 1000 units of 512 bytes read) and is "
"rounded up. When the LBA size is a value other than 512 bytes, the "
"controller converts the amount of data read to 512-byte units."
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:77
msgid ""
"The number of 512-byte data units the host has written to the controller. "
"This value does not include metadata. The value is reported in thousands "
"(i.e. a value of 1 corresponds to 1000 units of 512 bytes read) and is "
"rounded up."
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:82
msgid "Number of read commands completed by the controller"
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:85
msgid "Number of write commands completed by the controller"
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:88
msgid "The amount of time the controller is busy with I/O commands."
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:91
msgid "Number of power cycles experienced by the drive"
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:94
msgid ""
"Number of hours in power-on state. This does not include the time that the "
"controller was powered in a low power state condition."
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:97
msgid ""
"Number of unsafe shutdowns. This value is incremented when a shutdown "
"notification is not received prior to loss of power."
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:100
msgid ""
"Number of occurrences where the controller detected an unrecovered data "
"integrity error. Errors such as uncorrectable ECC, CRC checksum failure or "
"LBA tag mismatch are included in this field."
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:104
msgid ""
"Maximum number of possible Error Information Log entries preserved over the "
"life of the controller"
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:108
msgid ""
"The minimum Composite Temperature field value indicates an overheating "
"condition during which the controller operation continues. Immediate "
"remediation is recommended (e.g. additional cooling or workload reduction)."
msgstr ""

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:112
